{[show NESW]
[ROLE leader][STAGE pre-lead] Lead the \C6, fourth-best from your longest suit — the normal attack against 3NT.

[ROLE declarer][STAGE auction-end] Partner's 3\S was Smolen — five hearts and four spades — but with no fit you belong in 3NT, needing nine tricks. Your club suit is solid, the top hearts are ready, and the ninth trick must come from dummy's \SA-J-T-4 over your 9-8-5, missing BOTH the king and queen. Plan the DOUBLE FINESSE: lead spades toward dummy twice — the ten first, then toward the jack. One of the two rates to win, and one spade trick beyond the ace is all this contract asks.

[ROLE declarer][STAGE post-lead] West led the \C6, and your solid clubs win the first tricks. Now spades: low toward dummy's ten — East takes the KING. That was the first hook; the plan allows for it. Win the return and lead spades toward dummy again — this time West's QUEEN comes up, and dummy's ace captures it. Now the jack is the master spade: dummy's third-round winner. Two spade tricks, four clubs, the \HA-K, and a diamond make nine. Concede the rest and claim.

[ROLE declarer][STAGE post-play] Both missing honors made an appearance — the king beat your ten, then the queen walked into the ace on the second lead — and that is exactly how a double finesse cashes in: two chances instead of one, and only one loser in the suit. The ten lost so that the jack could rule. Nicely played.}
